According to our documentation [Bamboo variables|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO/Bamboo+variables], we provide the previous revision number from a repository (e.g.: bamboo.repository.previous.revision.number).

It would be beneficial if users were able to get the last successful revision from a repository in order to generate a build from it.

{{bamboo.repository.previous.successful.revision.number}}

I would kindly ask to update the following  [Application Links Version Matrix|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/APPLINKS/Application+Links+Version+Matrix] as the same seems to be outdated according to the following:

Product: *Stash 2.8.1*
Product: *Bamboo 5.1.1*

{code}
// <username>, an administrator user used to log in to Bamboo
// <password>, used to the username above
// <bamboo>, Bamboo baseURL
// <stash>, Stash baseURL
curl -u <username>:<password> http://<bamboo>/rest/applinks/1.0/applicationlinkForm/manifest.json?url=http://<stash>
{code}

{code:javascript|title=Output from command cURL above}
{"id":"e098bd48-1f1f-313a-8ecb-b135efdcc0a1","name":"Stash","typeId":"stash","version":"2.12.1","buildNumber":2012001,"applinksVersion":"4.1.1","inboundAuthenticationTypes":["com.atlassian.applinks.api.auth.types.TrustedAppsAuthenticationProvider","com.atlassian.applinks.api.auth.types.BasicAuthenticationProvider","com.atlassian.applinks.api.auth.types.OAuthAuthenticationProvider"],"outboundAuthenticationTypes":["com.atlassian.applinks.api.auth.types.TrustedAppsAuthenticationProvider","com.atlassian.applinks.api.auth.types.BasicAuthenticationProvider","com.atlassian.applinks.api.auth.types.OAuthAuthenticationProvider"],"publicSignup":false,"url":"http://<stash>","iconUrl":"http://<stash>/s/en_US/ee5019c/1/4.1.1/_/download/resources/com.atlassian.applinks.applinks-plugin:applinks-images/images/types/16stash.png"}
{code}

Currently when we are making the Backup at a daily basis with the Stash Backup Client and Bamboo is checking for changes it fails with an error message.

{quote}
(com.atlassian.bamboo.repository.RepositoryException : java.lang.RuntimeException: com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.stash.repository.StashRepositoryException: com.atlassian.bamboo.repository.RepositoryException: com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.git.GitCommandException: command 'C:\Program Files (x86)\Git\bin\git.exe' ls-remote ssh://3448c6b2-afda-43af-8c22-ef3fd88fae08@127.0.0.1:60328/lk/sourcen.git failed with code 128. Working directory was [.]., stderr: [Warning: Permanently added '[127.0.0.1]:60328' (RSA) to the list of known hosts., Stash is currently unavailable:, - The system is unavailable while maintenance is being performed., - Stash is unavailable while it is being backed up, fatal: Could not read from remote repository., , Please make sure you have the correct access rights, and the repository exists.])
{quote}

Bamboo should be so smart that if the Stash Backup Client is running it should not add a system error.
